!> The `consul.CatalogEntry` resource has been deprecated in version 2.0.0 of the provider
and will be removed in a future release. Please read the [upgrade guide](https://www.terraform.io/docs/providers/consul/guides/upgrading.html#deprecation-of-consul_catalog_entry)
for more information.

Registers a node or service with the [Consul Catalog](https://www.consul.io/docs/agent/http/catalog.html#catalog_register).
Currently, defining health checks is not supported.

using Pulumi;
using Consul = Pulumi.Consul;

class MyStack : Stack

    public MyStack()

        {
            Address = "192.168.10.10",
            Node = "foobar",
            Services = 
            {
                new Consul.Inputs.CatalogEntryServiceArgs
                {
                    Address = "127.0.0.1",
                    Id = "redis1",
                    Name = "redis",
                    Port = 8000,
                    Tags =

                        "master",
                        "v1",
                    },
                },
            },
        });
    }

}

package main

import (

func main() {
	pulumi.Run(func(ctx *pulumi.Context) error {
		_, err := consul.NewCatalogEntry(ctx, "app", &consul.CatalogEntryArgs{

			Node:    pulumi.String("foobar"),
			Services: consul.CatalogEntryServiceArray{
				&consul.CatalogEntryServiceArgs{
					Address: pulumi.String("127.0.0.1"),
					Id:      pulumi.String("redis1"),
					Name:    pulumi.String("redis"),
					Port:    pulumi.Int(8000),
					Tags: pulumi.StringArray{
						pulumi.String("master"),
						pulumi.String("v1"),
					},
				},
			},
		})
		if err != nil {
			return err
		}
		return nil
	})
}
